Q: Math CAPTCHA don&#39;t work with dividing - how to fix? A: <pre><code>def solve_math_captcha(captcha_text):
    match = re.search('(\d+)\s*([+-×\*÷/])\s(\d+)', captcha_text)
    if not match:
        return None
    num1, op, num2 = int(match.group(1)), match.group(2), int(match.group(3))
    ops = {'+': lambda a,b: a+b, '-': lambda a,b: a-b, '×': lambda a,b: a*b, '*': lambda a,b: a*b, '÷': lambda a,b: a//b, '/': lambda a,b: a//b}
    return ops.get(op, lambda a,b: a+b)(num1, num2)
</code></pre>

Q: Svelte barrel/index file throws TypeError &quot;Cannot find module...&quot; A: <p>TypeScript isn't recognizing <code>.svelte</code> files. Quick checks:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Make sure <code>icons/</code> is under <code>src/</code> SvelteKit's tsconfig only covers <code>src/</code> by default</p>
</li>
<li><p>Verify tsconfig.json extends the SvelteKit one:</p>
</li>
</ol>
<pre><code>{
  &quot;extends&quot;: &quot;./.svelte-kit/tsconfig.json&quot;
}
</code></pre>
<ol start="3">
<li>If still broken, add <code>src/svelte.d.ts</code>:</li>
</ol>
<pre><code>declare module '*.svelte' {
  import type { ComponentType } from 'svelte';
  const component: ComponentType;
  export default component;
}
</code></pre>
<p>Then restart TS server (Ctrl+Shift+P → &quot;TypeScript: Restart TS Server&quot;).</p>

Q: Nuxt /server auto-imported types not updating A: <hr />
<p>This is a known limitation Nitro doesn't regenerate <code>nitro-imports.d.ts</code> on file changes like Nuxt does for the client side.</p>
<p><strong>Quick workaround: Restart Nitro types manually</strong></p>
<p>Run <code>nuxi prepare</code> to regenerate types without full restart.</p>
<p><strong>Or trigger a regeneration with a nuxt.config change:</strong></p>
<p>Just save <code>nuxt.config.ts</code> (even without changes) this often kicks the type regeneration.</p>
<p><strong>Try enabling experimental typegen watching:</strong></p>
<p>nuxt.config.ts:</p>
<pre><code>export default defineNuxtConfig({
  nitro: {
    typescript: {
      generateTsConfig: true,
    },
  },
  experimental: {
    typedPages: true,
  },
})
</code></pre>
<p><strong>VS Code workaround:</strong></p>
<p>Restart the TypeScript server after adding new exports: Ctrl+Shift+P → &quot;TypeScript: Restart TS Server&quot;</p>
<p>This is a gap in Nitro's DX client-side auto-imports have better watch support than server-side. If none of these help, it's worth opening an issue on the Nitro repo since you can reproduce it across multiple projects.</p>
